---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---
<Layout title="PlantPal — Support" description="PlantPal support and help.">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-5 py-16">
    <a href="/" class="text-white/30 hover:text-white text-sm transition mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-1">
      ← Back to Home
    </a>
    
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-6 mb-2">Support — PlantPal</h1>
    <p class="text-white/30 mb-10">We're here to help your plants thrive.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">For questions, bug reports, or feature requests, email us at:</p>
    <p class="text-white mb-6"><a href="mailto:justinbundrick@gmail.com" class="text-green-400 hover:text-green-300 underline text-lg">justinbundrick@gmail.com</a></p>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">We typically respond within 24 hours.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">FAQ</h2>
    
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-3">How do I identify a plant?</h3>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Go to the Identify tab, take a photo or choose one from your library, and PlantPal's AI will identify the species with confidence ratings.</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-3">How accurate is the plant identification?</h3>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">PlantPal uses Plant.id, a leading plant identification AI. Accuracy varies by photo quality and species — clear, well-lit photos of leaves or flowers give the best results.</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-3">How do I cancel my subscription?</h3>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Open iPhone Settings → tap your name → Subscriptions → PlantPal → Cancel. You'll keep Pro access until the end of your billing period.</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-3">Will I lose my plants if I switch phones?</h3>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">If iCloud is enabled, your plants sync automatically across all your Apple devices. You can also export your plant collection as a backup from Settings.</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-3">How does the Light Meter work?</h3>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">The Light Meter uses your phone's camera to measure ambient light levels in lux. Point it at any spot to see which plants would thrive there. Pro feature.</p>
  </div>
</Layout>
